## Phased rollout framing

The codebase + ops posture is staged across four phases. Each phase lifts the bar without rewriting the previous one:

| Phase | Posture | What's true |
|---|---|---|
| **1 — validation** | single dev, manual deploys, no real customer traffic | trust bar is the only gate; no SLOs |
| **2 — early traffic** | invited beta users, manual deploys, basic monitoring | uptime is now a thing; rollback runbook required |
| **3 — paid product** | Stripe billing live, GitHub Actions deploys, eval gates in CI | revenue at stake; data-deletion SLA enforced |
| **4 — scale** | autoscaling, multi-region considerations, on-call rotation | classic prod posture |

Most decisions in this repo lock in defaults for Phase 1-2 with explicit doors for Phase 3-4. Don't speculatively bypass the current phase's defaults.

